  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I don't want to see leftover error messages when I return to a previous screen.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: The error message for an invalid contact code does not clear if the user navigates away from the new chat screen without either deleting or correcting the code.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nError message disappears once a user navigates to any other screen. \r\n\r\nOn returning to the \"Start new chat\" screen, the contact code field should not display an error.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # \r\nWhen the user returns to the \"Start new chat\" screen, the error message still appears but the text has been cleared.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/39475299-0ac5d976-4d58-11e8-90af-43d13253692c.png\" width=\"300\">\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # \r\n\r\n- Start new chat\r\n- Begin typing any invalid contact code\r\n- Go back OR to recent contact OR QR code\r\n- Return to \"Start new chat\" screen \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Develop 2018-05-01\r\n* Operating System: iOS",
